SIMPLE: fantastic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fantastic
<hw>Fan*tas"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>fantastique</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/ able
to represent, fr. <?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/ to make visible. See
<er>Fancy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Existing only in imagination;
fanciful; imaginary; not real; chimerical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having the nature of a phantom; unreal.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Indulging the vagaries of imagination; whimsical;
full of absurd fancies; capricious; <as>as, <ex>fantastic</ex> minds; a
<ex>fantastic</ex> mistress.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Resembling fantasies in irregularity, caprice, or
eccentricity; irregular; oddly shaped; grotesque.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There at the foot of yonder nodding beech,⟦br⟧
That wreathes its old <qex>fantastic</qex> roots so high.</q>
<rj><qau>T. Gray.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Fanciful; imaginative; ideal; visionary;
capricious; chimerical; whimsical; queer. See
<er>Fanciful</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fantastic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fantastic
<hw>Fan*tas"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person given to fantastic
dress, manners, etc.; an eccentric person; a fop.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our <qex>fantastics</qex>, who, having a fine watch, take all
ocasions to draw it out to be seen.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fantastical</ent>⟦br⟧
